\"margin-left:13px; line-height:150%\"\n|align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"|a.\n|{{note|status}}{{Kosovo-note}}\n|}\n\n{{Football in Kosovo}}\n{{List of football clubs in Europe}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in Kosovo| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of association football clubs|Kosovo]]\n[[Category:Kosovo sport-related lists|Football clubs]]\n", "name_user": "WDM10", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eIpko Superliga", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_football_clubs_in_Kosovo"}
{"title_page": "Kr\u00f6llwitz", "text_new": "{{Infobox German location\n|name           = Kr\u00f6llwitz\n|name_local     =\n|image_photo    = Halle7.jpg\n|image_caption  = View over Kr\u00f6llwitz from Giebichenstein Castle\n|type           = Quarter\n|City           = Halle (Saale)\n|image_coa      = \n|coordinates    = {{coord|51|30|20|N|11|56|59|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|state          = Saxony-Anhalt\n|district       =\n|borough        = West\n|divisions      =\n|B\u00fcrgermeistertitel =\n|mayor          =\n|elevation      =\n|area           =\n|population     = 5445\n|population_as_of = 2015-12-31\n|postal_code    = 06120\n|area_code      =\n|licence        = HAL\n|year           = 1291\n|plantext       = Location of Kr\u00f6llwitz in Halle (Saale)\n|image_plan     = Halle_(Saale)_Stadtteil_5_91.svg\n|website        =\n}}\n'''Kr\u00f6llwitz''' is a [[village]] and locality (''Ortsteil'') in the West borough (''Stadtbezirk West'') of [[Halle (Saale)]]. It is located in the [[Germany|German]] state [[Saxony-Anhalt]].<ref>[http://www.halle.de/VeroeffentlichungenBinaries/691/960/halle_in_zahlen_2015.pdf Halle in Zahlen 2015]</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe center of Kr\u00f6llwitz is located on a hill. There is the Petruskirche and the primary school of Kr\u00f6llwitz. A part of [[Weinberg Campus]], one of the biggest technology parks in eastern Germany, is located in the southern part of the quarter. The hospital of the [[Martin Luther University of Halle-Wittenberg]] takes a big area between the old part of Kr\u00f6llwitz and Weinberg Campus.\nIn the east, it is bordered by the river [[Saale]]. In the north, you can see the Ochsenberg (english: 'oxen mountain').\n==History==\nKr\u00f6llwitz was mentioned as Crolewitz in 1291 for the first time. It was a [[Sorbs|sorbian]] fisher village.\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n{{Navbox\n| name       = Kr\u00f6llwitz\n| title      = Boroughs and quarters in Halle (Saale)\n| listclass  = hlist\n| state      = {{{Germany|}}}\n\n| above      =\n| image      =\n\n| group1     = Central borough ''(Stadtbezirk Mitte)''\n| list1      = [[Altstadt (Halle)|Altstadt]], [[S\u00fcdliche Innenstadt (Halle)|S\u00fcdliche Innenstadt]], [[N\u00f6rdliche Innenstadt (Halle)|N\u00f6rdliche Innenstadt]]\n\n| group2     = North borough ''(Stadtbezirk Nord)''\n| list2      = [[Paulusviertel]], [[Am Wasserturm/Thaerviertel]], [[Landrain]], [[Frohe Zukunft]], [[Trotha]], [[Industriegebiet Nord (Halle)|Industriegebiet Nord]], [[Gottfried-Keller-Siedlung]], [[Giebichenstein (Halle)|Giebichenstein]], [[Seeben]], [[Tornau (Halle)|Tornau]], [[M\u00f6tzlich]]\n\n| group3     = East borough ''(Stadtbezirk Ost)''\n| list3      = [[Gebiet der DR]], [[Freiimfelde/Kanenaer Weg]], [[Dieselstra\u00dfe]], [[Diemitz]], [[Dautzsch]], [[Reideburg|Reideburg]], [[B\u00fcschdorf]], [[Kanena/Bruckdorf]]\n\n| group4     = South borough ''(Stadtbezirk S\u00fcd)''\n| list4      = [[Lutherplatz/Th\u00fcringer Bahnhof]], [[Gesundbrunnen (Halle)|Gesundbrunnen]], [[S\u00fcdstadt (Halle)|S\u00fcdstadt]], [[Damaschkestra\u00dfe]], [[Ammendorf/Beesen]], [[Radewell/Osendorf]], [[Planena]], [[B\u00f6llberg/W\u00f6rmlitz]], [[Silberh\u00f6he]]\n\n| group5     = West borough ''(Stadtbezirk West)''\n| list5      = [[N\u00f6rdliche Neustadt]], [[S\u00fcdliche Neustadt]], [[Westliche Neustadt]], [[Gewerbegebiet Neustadt]], [[Lettin (Halle)|Lettin]], [[Heide-Nord/Blumenau]], [[Saaleaue (Halle)|Saaleaue]], [[Kr\u00f6llwitz]], [[Heide-S\u00fcd]], [[Nietleben]], [[D\u00f6lauer Heide]], [[D\u00f6lau]]\n\n<!-- ... -->\n\n| below      = Main article: [[Boroughs and quarters in Halle (Saale)]]\n}}\n[[Category:Towns in Saxony-Anhalt]]\n[[Category:Halle (Saale)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox German location\n|name           = Kr\u00f6llwitz\n|name_local     =\n|image_photo    = Halle7.jpg\n|image_caption  = View over Kr\u00f6llwitz from Giebichenstein Castle\n|of_city_coa    = Coat_of_arms_of_Halle_(Saale).svg\n|type           = Quarter\n|article_       = of\n|City           = Halle (Saale)\n|Town           =\n|image_coa      = \n|map_           =\n|map_cap        =\n|coordinates    = {{coord|51|30|20|N|11|56|59|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|state          = Saxony-Anhalt\n|district       =\n|borough        = West\n|divisions      =\n|_office        =\n|B\u00fcrgermeistertitel =\n|mayor          =\n|elevation      =\n|area           =\n|population     = 5445\n|population_as_of = 2015-12-31\n|density        = \n|pop_ref        =\n|postal_code    = 06120\n|area_code      =\n|licence        = HAL\n|free_2         =\n|free_2_txt     =\n|year           = 1291\n|plantext       = Location of Kr\u00f6llwitz in Halle (Saale)\n|image_plan     = Halle_(Saale)_Stadtteil_5_91.svg\n|website        =\n}}\n'''Kr\u00f6llwitz''' is a [[village]] and locality (''Ortsteil'') in the West borough (''Stadtbezirk West'') of [[Halle (Saale)]]. It is located in the [[Germany|German]] state [[Saxony-Anhalt]].<ref>[http://www.halle.de/VeroeffentlichungenBinaries/691/960/halle_in_zahlen_2015.pdf Halle in Zahlen 2015]</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe center of Kr\u00f6llwitz is located on a hill. There is the Petruskirche and the primary school of Kr\u00f6llwitz. A part of [[Weinberg Campus]], one of the biggest technology parks in eastern Germany, is located in the southern part of the quarter. The hospital of the [[Martin Luther University of Halle-Wittenberg]] takes a big area between the old part of Kr\u00f6llwitz and Weinberg Campus.\nIn the east, it is bordered by the river [[Saale]]. In the north, you can see the Ochsenberg (english: 'oxen mountain').\n==History==\nKr\u00f6llwitz was mentioned as Crolewitz in 1291 for the first time. It was a [[Sorbs|sorbian]] fisher village.\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n{{Navbox\n| name       = Kr\u00f6llwitz\n| title      = Boroughs and quarters in Halle (Saale)\n| listclass  = hlist\n| state      = {{{Germany|}}}\n\n| above      =\n| image      =\n\n| group1     = Central borough ''(Stadtbezirk Mitte)''\n| list1      = [[Altstadt (Halle)|Altstadt]], [[S\u00fcdliche Innenstadt (Halle)|S\u00fcdliche Innenstadt]], [[N\u00f6rdliche Innenstadt (Halle)|N\u00f6rdliche Innenstadt]]\n\n| group2     = North borough ''(Stadtbezirk Nord)''\n| list2      = [[Paulusviertel]], [[Am Wasserturm/Thaerviertel]], [[Landrain]], [[Frohe Zukunft]], [[Trotha]], [[Industriegebiet Nord (Halle)|Industriegebiet Nord]], [[Gottfried-Keller-Siedlung]], [[Giebichenstein (Halle)|Giebichenstein]], [[Seeben]], [[Tornau (Halle)|Tornau]], [[M\u00f6tzlich]]\n\n| group3     = East borough ''(Stadtbezirk Ost)''\n| list3      = [[Gebiet der DR]], [[Freiimfelde/Kanenaer Weg]], [[Dieselstra\u00dfe]], [[Diemitz]], [[Dautzsch]], [[Reideburg|Reideburg]], [[B\u00fcschdorf]], [[Kanena/Bruckdorf]]\n\n| group4     = South borough ''(Stadtbezirk S\u00fcd)''\n| list4      = [[Lutherplatz/Th\u00fcringer Bahnhof]], [[Gesundbrunnen (Halle)|Gesundbrunnen]], [[S\u00fcdstadt (Halle)|S\u00fcdstadt]], [[Damaschkestra\u00dfe]], [[Ammendorf/Beesen]], [[Radewell/Osendorf]], [[Planena]], [[B\u00f6llberg/W\u00f6rmlitz]], [[Silberh\u00f6he]]\n\n| group5     = West borough ''(Stadtbezirk West)''\n| list5      = [[N\u00f6rdliche Neustadt]], [[S\u00fcdliche Neustadt]], [[Westliche Neustadt]], [[Gewerbegebiet Neustadt]], [[Lettin (Halle)|Lettin]], [[Heide-Nord/Blumenau]], [[Saaleaue (Halle)|Saaleaue]], [[Kr\u00f6llwitz]], [[Heide-S\u00fcd]], [[Nietleben]], [[D\u00f6lauer Heide]], [[D\u00f6lau]]\n\n<!-- ... -->\n\n| below      = Main article: [[Boroughs and quarters in Halle (Saale)]]\n}}\n[[Category:Towns in Saxony-Anhalt]]\n[[Category:Halle (Saale)]]\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kr%C3%B6llwitz"}
{"title_page": "If the World Was Ending", "text_new": "{{short description|Song by JP Saxe featuring Julia Michaels}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = If the World Was Ending\n| cover         = If the World Was Ending by Saxe and Michaels.png\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[JP Saxe]] featuring [[Julia Michaels]]\n| EP            = Hold It Together\n| released      = {{Start date|2019|10|19|mf=yes}}\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded      = July 2019\n| genre         = \n| length        = {{Duration|m=3|s=28}}\n| label         = [[Arista Records|Arista]]\n| writer        = {{hlist|[[JP Saxe|Jonathan Percy Starker Saxe]]|[[Julia Michaels]]<ref name=\"Tidal\">{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/119496335/credits|title=Credits / If the World Was Ending (feat. Julia Michaels) / Jp Saxe|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>}}\n| producer      = [[Finneas O'Connell|Finneas]]<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n| chronology    = [[JP Saxe]]\n| prev_title    = Women Who Look Like You\n| prev_year     = 2019\n| next_title    = Sad Corny F**k\n| next_year     = 2020\n| misc          = {{Extra chronology\n| artist        = [[Julia Michaels]]\n| type          = single \n| prev_title    = [[If You Need Me (Julia Michaels song)|If You Need Me]]\n| prev_year     = 2019\n| title         = If the World Was Ending\n| year          = 2019\n| next_title    = [[Cool Anymore]]\n| next_year     = 2019\n}}{{External music video|{{YouTube|1jO2wSpAoxA|title=\"If the World Was Ending\"}}|type=single}}\n}}\n\n\"'''If the World Was Ending'''\" is a song by Canadian singer [[JP Saxe]], featuring vocals of American singer [[Julia Michaels]]. The song was released by [[Arista Records]] on October 19, 2019, through digital download and streaming formats.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/if-the-world-was-ending-feat-julia-michaels-single/1482468336|title=If the World Was Ending \u2013 Single|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=October 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSpeaking to [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']], Michaels said \"I discovered JP's music and posted about him around the same time he was listening to ''[[Inner Monologue Part 1|Inner Monologue]]''. Since we were fans of each other's music, we got together for a writing session.\" Saxe added \"Writing this song with Julia was one of the most creative experiences of my life. We wrote it the day we met and recorded it that same day.\"<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8533210/jp-saxe-julia-michaels-if-the-world-was-ending-video |title=JP Saxe & Julia Michaels Prepare For the Apocalypse in 'If The World Was Ending' Video: Watch |website=Billboard|date= October 17, 2019|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMichaels said \"The song is about that person in your life who you would come back to if the world was ending, when nothing else matters and there is nothing left to hold you back.\"<ref name=\"Billboard\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\n'''Digital download'''\n# \"If the World Was Ending\" \u2013 3:28\n\n'''Remixes'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/if-the-world-was-ending-feat-julia-michaels-remixes-single/1499729618|title=If the World Was Ending (Remixes) \u2013 Single by JP Saxe on Apple Music|website=Apple Music|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n# \"If the World Was Ending\" ([[Marian Hill]] remix) \u2013 3:27\n# \"If the World Was Ending\" (Other remix) \u2013 2:29\n# \"If the World Was Ending\" (Original) \u2013 3:28\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2020/1/aria-chart-watch-560/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #560|publisher=auspOp|date=January 18, 2020|accessdate=